
Som naevnt tidligere, har jeg behov for at kunne indramme og separere items
i vinduer omfattende multiple interface objekter. For at kunne goere 
dette i en stil der stemmer overens med de forskellige platforme er det 
ikke oenskeligt direkte at skulle tegne sig til disse separatorer, og jeg 
mener derfor at funktionaliteten boer understoettes direkte af uienv.

Nedenfor foelger et par udetaljerede forslag til hvad det er jeg oensker, 
nemlig en mekanisme til at indramme ting, og en mekanisme til
at separere ting. Da jeg mener ikke at kunne klare mig uden ved implementation
af ny valhalla, ser jeg gerne support for nedenstaaende implementeret saa 
snart som det nu kan lade sig goere.

De mulige vaerdier af separator.type er taget direkte fra 
motif/separatorgadget.bet, men jeg mener egt. det er et meget fornuftigt
udvalg.

Kommentarer?

  -- Soren

framed: canvas
  (# type:
       (* value is one of the following:
        * 
        *   + UIENV_SHADOW_ETCHED_IN - frame giving the effect of a
        *     region etched into the window. 
        *   + UIENV_SHADOW_ETCHED_OUT - frame giving the effect of a
        *     region coming out of the window. 
        *)
       (# value: @Integer;
       enter value
       do ...
       #);
     contentsType:< canvas
       (# open::<
            (# 
            do ... -> size;
               INNER;
            #);
       #);
     ...
  #);

separator: windowitem
  (# type:  
       (* Specifies the type of line drawing to be done in
        * THIS(separator):
        *   + UIENV_SINGLE_LINE - single line.
        *   + UIENV_DOUBLE_LINE - double line.
        *   + UIENV_SINGLE_DASHED_LINE - single-dashed line.
        *   + UIENV_DOUBLE_DASHED_LINE - double-dashed line.
        *   + UIENV_NO_LINE - no line.
        *   + UIENV_SHADOW_ETCHED_IN - double line giving the effect of a
        *     line etched into the window. The thickness of the double
        *     line is equal to the value of shadowThickness.  For
        *     horizontal orientation, the top line is drawn in
        *     topShadowColor and the bottom line is drawn in
        *     bottomShadowColor. For vertical orientation, the left line
        *     is drawn in topShadowColor and the right line is drawn in
        *     bottomShadowColor.
        *   + UIENV_SHADOW_ETCHED_OUT - double line giving the effect of
        *     an etched line coming out from the window. The thickness of
        *     the double line is equal to the value of shadowThickness.
        *     For horizontal orientation, the top line is drawn in
        *     bottomShadowColor and the bottom line is drawn in
        *     topShadowColor. For vertical orientation, the left line is
        *     drawn in bottomShadowColor and the right line is drawn in
        *     topShadowColor.
        *)
       (# value: @Integer;
       enter value
       do ...
       #);
  #);




